Effective Date: May 29, 2025
Developer: kanaads
App Name: TwinMind Internship App

1. Information We Collect
The app may collect the following data from users:

Google Account Info: Name, email address (for login/authentication purposes)

Google Calendar Data: Events and metadata (with user permission)

Microphone Audio: For transcription (processed in real-time and not stored permanently)

All data access is done with the user’s explicit permission using Google’s secure OAuth sign-in.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data to:

Authenticate users via Google Sign-In

Display upcoming meetings via Google Calendar

Transcribe meetings in real-time for your use

Enable AI-powered chat and summary generation

3. Data Storage
User data may be temporarily stored locally on the device.

Audio transcriptions may be processed via secure APIs (e.g., OpenAI, Google Gemini).

No personal data is sold or shared with third parties.

4. Your Consent
By using the app, you consent to:

The collection and use of your data as described above

Integration with Google and OpenAI services

